   <p>Use a single text input by itself if the only way people can get the service is if they enter their NHS number.</p>
   <p>Use a single text input labelled either "what is your NHS number?" or "enter your NHS number".</p>
   <p><a href='/service-manual/content/how-to-write-good-questions-for-forms/write-the-supporting-content-for-your-form#help-text'>Provide help text</a> to make sure users recognise their NHS number and know the correct details to enter.</p>
   <p>Provide guidance on where users can find their NHS number as soon as possible, preferably before the user has started the service as well as during the journey.</p>
   <p>It is recommended to always have an alternative way for users to continue with their journey.</p>

