<p>Use a question before a single text input if:</p>
<ul>
    <li>there is another way for users to continue without an NHS number.</li>
    <li>the NHS number route is likely to be more successful for the user.</li>
</ul>

<p>Use a 2-option radio button that asks the user if they know their NHS number. If they do, route them to a page that asks for their NHS number. If they do not, route them to a page that asks for alternative details, for example, a combination of other personal details like a user's postcode and date of birth.</p>
<p>Provide help text on both NHS number route pages to help them find their NHS number and confirm they have the right format.</p>

