<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

    <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-6">How to use the NHS number pattern</h2>
    <p>When asking for an NHS number:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>use a text input that allows for spaces and other characters between numbers. Some users will copy the format the NHS number is printed in (3-3-4) and include spaces.</li>
        <li>give clear guidance on what an NHS number looks like</li>
        <li>allow at least 12 characters in your NHS number input</li>
        <li class="rich-text">add the <code>inputmode='numeric'</code> attribute to your input to provide mobile users with a numeric keyboard on iOS devices and mobile Chrome</li>
        <li>validate the NHS number by using a modulus 11 algorithm to check if the number is valid</li>
    </ul>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

    <h3>Give users clear guidance where they can find their NHS number</h3>
    <p>Users are more likely to be successful in their journey the earlier you mention that they need an NHS number, along with where to find it.</p>
    <p>Provide guidance where to find it before the user starts the service, as well as within the service itself.</p>
    <p>For example:</p>


    <details class="nhsuk-details nhsuk-expander">
  <summary class="nhsuk-details__summary">
    <span class="nhsuk-details__summary-text">
      How to find your NHS number
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="nhsuk-details__text">
    <p>An NHS number is a 10 digit number, like 485 777 3456.</p>
    <p>You can find your NHS number by logging in to a GP online service or on any document sent to you by the NHS, such as your:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>prescriptions</li>
        <li>test results</li>
        <li>hospital referral letters</li>
        <li>appointment letters</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Ask your GP surgery for help if you can't find your NHS number.</p>
  </div>
</details>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

    <h3>Use the correct NHS number format</h3>
    <p>Write the NHS number as 3 groups of numbers, with a single space between them, like this: 485 777 3456.</p>
    <p>Keep the NHS number on 1 line - do not allow it to break over 2 lines.</p>
    <p>Read more about how to format the NHS number in <a href='/service-manual/content/a-to-z-of-NHS-health-writing'>the A to Z of NHS health writing</a>.</p>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

    <h3>Write clear error messages</h3>
    <p>Make sure you use <a href='/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/error-summary'>error summaries</a> and clear <a href='/service-manual/styles-components-patterns/error-message'>error messages</a> when you ask users for their NHS number.</p>


